						               													<description>&amp;ldquo;Numeri&amp;hellip; che pizza!&amp;rdquo; is a game in which children can learn to count, make the first additions and even develop memory.&amp;#10;The box contains 24 slices of pizza of different sizes, 2 pizza containers, 2 dice and 5 hats. Each slice has a number from 1 to 4 on one side and an ingredient with the respective quantity on the other. For example, on one side there is the number 3 and on the other there are 3 mushrooms. Some slices are rotten.&amp;#10;The current player rolls the 2 dice (which show an ingredient and a number) and takes the corresponding segment.&amp;#10;The game includes 3 modes:&amp;#10;- Basic mode (for 2 players aged 4+): whoever completes a pizza first earns a hat. To complete a pizza you have to take exactly 10 ingredients. The winner is the first player with 3 hats.&amp;#10;- Complete mode (for 2 players aged 5+): compared to the previous mode, the slices should be placed face down on the side with the number. As a result, children should remember the ingredients below and avoid rotten pizza slices.&amp;#10;- Cooperative mode (for 1 or more players aged 5+): the children collaborate and try to complete a pizza before that rotten pizza is formed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
